    <!-- COST SECTION -->
    <section>
        <h2>Average Cost of Roof Repair in Ohio</h2>
        <p>The cost to repair your roof varies based on the type of damage, materials, and roof size. Most Ohio homeowners pay between $500–$1,500 for common repairs, with the average being around $1,200. Here's what impacts pricing:</p>
        
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Missing or damaged shingles:</strong> $150–$500. Replacing a few shingles is relatively inexpensive, but specialty or premium shingles cost more.</li>
            <li><strong>Roof leaks and flashing repair:</strong> $300–$1,000+. Flashing is crucial to preventing leaks. Repair cost depends on location, material, and extent of damage.</li>
            <li><strong>Soffit and fascia repair:</strong> $500–$2,000+. These structural elements protect your roof and attic. Repairs can be complex and expensive depending on damage extent.</li>
            <li><strong>Ice dam removal and prevention:</strong> $400–$1,500. Complex jobs requiring professional equipment and attic ventilation improvements.</li>
            <li><strong>Roof vent replacement:</strong> $150–$600. Cost depends on vent type, location, and damage extent.</li>
            <li><strong>Truss or roof decking repair:</strong> $1,000–$5,000+. Structural damage is expensive due to complexity and materials.</li>
            <li><strong>Premium materials (slate, tile, metal):</strong> Higher repair costs due to material and labor specialization.</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p><strong>Always get a professional estimate before proceeding.</strong> We provide free inspections and transparent quotes with no hidden fees.</p>
    </section>

